invalid type: string "Error messages are usually made up of a \n\t\tmsgnum element (the error code) and a \n\t\tmsgph or \n\t\tmsgblock element. Likewise, status messages are best\n\t\tdescribed with \n\t\tmsgph or \n\t\tmsgblock. The result displayed on a calculator after a\n\t\tuser has entered an equation is best described with a \n\t\tsystemoutput element. \n\t \n to substitute\n\t\tr = 55\nen